Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi Sells $1 Billion of Debt in Two Parts

-- B y   A s h l e y   L u t z
-- 
2011-02-15T21:51:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/bank-of-tokyo-mitsubishi-sells-1-billion-of-debt-in-two-parts.html
Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd.
sold $1 billion of three-year notes in a two-part offering,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.   The bank sold $500 million of floating-rate debt that paid
a spread of 66 basis points more than the London interbank
offered rate, the data show. It also sold $500 million of three-
year, 2.25 percent fixed-rate debt that paid a spread of 87.5
basis points more than similar-maturity U.S. Treasuries, the
data show.  A basis point is 0.01 of a percentage point. Libor, a
lending benchmark, was set at 0.31 percent today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ashley Lutz in New York at 
 alutz8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
